{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# RC2b: snapshot-horizon-safe replay (no silent sub-horizon drop)\n\n## Why\nWhen two clones write at once, one can compact (snapshot) and delete the events it folded before it\nhas seen the other's event. After the histories merge, that other event sorts BEFORE the snapshot,\nand replay's positional skip throws it away regardless of `source_event_uuids` -> silent data loss.\nThe live store still holds ~11 such KNOWN-type orphans.\n\n## Decision (ACCEPTED): Option 1 (rebuild-on-stray) + Option 3 (conservative horizon) first-line\nThe earlier \"apply the orphan / dedup by uuid\" idea was refuted (a full-state snapshot overwrites the\norphan, or the stale orphan wrongly wins). Accepted approach:\n- **Option 1 (ACCEPTED) — rebuild the snapshot when a stray shows up.** Keep folded events (A1\n  `.retired`) instead of deleting; when fsck detects a stray pre-snapshot event, rebuild that ticket's\n  snapshot from full history so the stray lands in its true position. Reuses A1 `.retired` + A3's\n  rebuild path; matches event-sourcing/git-bug (snapshot = rebuildable cache).\n- **Option 3 (ACCEPTED, first line) — don't compact the hot edge.** Only fold events old enough that\n  no concurrent writer could still land behind them, so rebuilds stay rare.\n- Deferred: Option 2 (per-field LWW-by-timestamp) — ideal end-state but biggest blast radius (~5\n  handlers + snapshot schema); tracked as a possible follow-up, not this ticket.\n\n## Scope\nReducer replay + snapshot handling (`reducer/_processors.py` process_snapshot + positional skip\n~648-702; `reducer/_sort.py`) + the fsck-triggered rebuild path (shared with A3). NOT the reconciler\ncode. Depends on A1.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Conservative-horizon (Option 3): compaction folds only \"settled\" events; rule documented.\n- [ ] Rebuild-on-stray (Option 1): fsck detects a merged-in pre-snapshot orphan and rebuilds the snapshot from the full ordered log (incl. `.retired`).\n- [ ] A merged-in pre-horizon orphan (uuid not in `source_event_uuids`) is no longer silently dropped.\n- [ ] Two-clone sub-horizon-append data-loss regression test: RED before, GREEN after.\n- [ ] Replay remains a pure function of the on-disk file set (determinism across clones preserved).\n- [ ] Decision + design recorded in an ADR.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783472202270534001,"uuid":"b7e62ab4-08cd-4958-9281-9ef1c38f2242"}